snippet.textDisplay:
Mark, you’re missing humidity. Add a humidifier or something to counteract the moisture taken out by the dry ice. Without the humidity the updraft of your fans can’t make a good funnel. Finally a fan pointing up from the ground as well as a fan lifted off the ground pointing up (with maybe one smaller fan pointing down to help downdraft) could help funnel it better.
I am not meteorologist, I just lived in Nebraska long enough to know that without that humidity ain’t nothing gonna form right.
